{"key":"post-6849875","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6849875</id>\n<content>You still have glare.  Never hold a jar in your hand to take pictures.  It's hard enough to hold a camera still, and it's hard to hold a jar still, but trying to do both amplifies the movement.  Use a tripod or a book to set the camera on, ditto for the jar, and then use a light other than the camera flash to take the picture.  All a flash does is relfect light back into the camera lense.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is what a picture of a colonizing jar should look like.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-10/329565823-colonizing_brf_jars_004a.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-10/329565823-thumb_colonizing_brf_jars_004a.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6849895</next>\n<prev>6849782</prev>\n<first>6849365</first>\n<last>6870879</last>\n<when>1177882529</when>\n<utime>04/30/07 12:35 AM</utime>\n</post>"}